# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: BlackMonolith | Scene: TheBlackMonolithWarrior1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "The army marched on Sarah's suspicion, and in less than a day, they encroached upon the outer limits of the city of Nauyziri."
    new "The army marched on Sarah's suspicion, and in less than a day, they encroached upon the outer limits of the city of Nauyziri."

    old "As far east as civilization had ever gone, the city had been one of the first to be abandoned when the empire of Bagrad receded."
    new "As far east as civilization had ever gone, the city had been one of the first to be abandoned when the empire of Bagrad receded."

    old "Once a favorite destination for the wealthy and elites to go on vacation, the city had been of little strategic interest to the empire."
    new "Once a favorite destination for the wealthy and elites to go on vacation, the city had been of little strategic interest to the empire."

    old "It had sat upon a great reservoir, causing many lakes to spring up around it, and painting the land green."
    new "It had sat upon a great reservoir, causing many lakes to spring up around it, and painting the land green."

    old "Those days were long gone, and only the desert remained."
    new "Those days were long gone, and only the desert remained."

    old "Centuries of disrepair had turned the once impressive city into a ruin of itself."
    new "Centuries of disrepair had turned the once impressive city into a ruin of itself."

    old "During the height of the Bagrad empire, it had earned itself the nickname, City of Knives, for the many plots and coups that had been born here."
    new "During the height of the Bagrad empire, it had earned itself the nickname, City of Knives, for the many plots and coups that had been born here."

    old "For the elites and nobles enjoyed vacationing almost as much as they enjoyed to scheme."
    new "For the elites and nobles enjoyed vacationing almost as much as they enjoyed to scheme."

    old "But no plots were born here. Not anymore."
    new "But no plots were born here. Not anymore."

    old "As the army drew nearer to the city, Sarah felt her heart soar at the sight of life."
    new "As the army drew nearer to the city, Sarah felt her heart soar at the sight of life."

    old "Small plumes of smoke hinted that there were other people."
    new "Small plumes of smoke hinted that there were other people."

    old "If the Mythran army had not been here, as Vaelen had said, with its many supplies, Sarah feared that even the miracle of the lake would not save them."
    new "If the Mythran army had not been here, as Vaelen had said, with its many supplies, Sarah feared that even the miracle of the lake would not save them."

    old "As the army made its way through the outskirts and into the proper center of the city, they soon came upon the first Mythran soldiers."
    new "As the army made its way through the outskirts and into the proper center of the city, they soon came upon the first Mythran soldiers."

    old "They were greeted with a mixture of surprise and bemusement."
    new "They were greeted with a mixture of surprise and bemusement."

    old "Her own troops had been run ragged by the desert, their skins blistered and a deep red."
    new "Her own troops had been run ragged by the desert, their skins blistered and a deep red."

    old "By contrast, the Mythran troops appeared in good spirits, well fed and jovial."
    new "By contrast, the Mythran troops appeared in good spirits, well fed and jovial."

    old "As they marched along the main road, the city eventually parted, giving way to a large open square."
    new "As they marched along the main road, the city eventually parted, giving way to a large open square."

    old "If she struggled, Sarah could see the remnants of a great city."
    new "If she struggled, Sarah could see the remnants of a great city."

    old "Far more eastern, even than Bagrad, the city of Nauyziri had suffered the advance of the desert for far longer, and more intensely."
    new "Far more eastern, even than Bagrad, the city of Nauyziri had suffered the advance of the desert for far longer, and more intensely."

    old "If Bagrad was a shadow of its former self, then on Nauyziri was a spectral shade."
    new "If Bagrad was a shadow of its former self, then on Nauyziri was a spectral shade."

    old "Caved in houses. Cracks than ran through the road. A long unused fountain, partially buried in the sand."
    new "Caved in houses. Cracks than ran through the road. A long unused fountain, partially buried in the sand."

    old "People used to live here, and they had lived well. This was all that remained."
    new "People used to live here, and they had lived well. This was all that remained."

    old "From the corner of her eyes, Sarah saw something surprising."
    new "From the corner of her eyes, Sarah saw something surprising."

    old "Green."
    new "Green."

    old "In the midsts of all this, even this far out, a solitary plant had buried its way through the earth."
    new "In the midsts of all this, even this far out, a solitary plant had buried its way through the earth."

    old "Even in a place like this, life could exist."
    new "Even in a place like this, life could exist."

    old "Studying the plant, she realized she'd never seen or read of any like it in her life."
    new "Studying the plant, she realized she'd never seen or read of any like it in her life."

    old "Perhaps in a different life, she would have collected such a thing. Brought it back to Rosanna to show to her family."
    new "Perhaps in a different life, she would have collected such a thing. Brought it back to Rosanna to show to her family."

    old "Plants and flowers could still move her, but Sarah had no illusions about what she was. A soldier."
    new "Plants and flowers could still move her, but Sarah had no illusions about what she was. A soldier."

    old "And soldiers didn't collect and categorize plants."
    new "And soldiers didn't collect and categorize plants."

    old "Looking away from the plant, Sarah suddenly saw a man marching across the square."
    new "Looking away from the plant, Sarah suddenly saw a man marching across the square."

    old "Finally, what seemed like a welcome."
    new "Finally, what seemed like a welcome."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Welcome, you are the mercenary company, I imagine?"
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Welcome, you are the mercenary company, I imagine?"

    old "Sarah looked across the square, everywhere her men were already setting up their camps."
    new "Sarah looked across the square, everywhere her men were already setting up their camps."

    old "Usually, it was Vaelen who would undertake such meetings, but she had no idea where he was."
    new "Usually, it was Vaelen who would undertake such meetings, but she had no idea where he was."

    old "Yes, we're the mercenary company, unless you were expecting anybody else out here on the other side of the world."
    new "Yes, we're the mercenary company, unless you were expecting anybody else out here on the other side of the world."

    old "The officer smiled."
    new "The officer smiled."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"No, only crazy folk this far out in the world."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"No, only crazy folk this far out in the world."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"And you are in charge?"
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"And you are in charge?"

    old "He eyed her, somewhat suspicious that a woman would lead a mercenary company."
    new "He eyed her, somewhat suspicious that a woman would lead a mercenary company."

    old "No, but I'm high up enough you might as well talk to me. I'll relay it back to our commander."
    new "No, but I'm high up enough you might as well talk to me. I'll relay it back to our commander."

    old "The officer nodded."
    new "The officer nodded."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Fair, makes my job easier."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Fair, makes my job easier."

    old "Sarah walked up closer to the man."
    new "Sarah walked up closer to the man."

    old "Tell me, no that I'll pass up on free money or anything, but what exactly are we doing all the way out here?"
    new "Tell me, no that I'll pass up on free money or anything, but what exactly are we doing all the way out here?"

    old "Sarah had spoken to Vaelen on more than one occasion about it, but he had been reluctant about telling her much of anything."
    new "Sarah had spoken to Vaelen on more than one occasion about it, but he had been reluctant about telling her much of anything."

    old "The officer regarded her for a moment."
    new "The officer regarded her for a moment."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Need-to-know-only. You just focus on supporting the security situation."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Need-to-know-only. You just focus on supporting the security situation."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Ooh, and I doubt you'll see much action, but there are some tribesmen that like to poke at our outer line, try and sneak into the city."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Ooh, and I doubt you'll see much action, but there are some tribesmen that like to poke at our outer line, try and sneak into the city."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Having some extra hands to secure the outter perimeter will work wonders."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Having some extra hands to secure the outter perimeter will work wonders."

    old "Sarah furrowed her brow, looking at him with a degree of confusion."
    new "Sarah furrowed her brow, looking at him with a degree of confusion."

    old "Tribesmen? On this side of the ocean?"
    new "Tribesmen? On this side of the ocean?"

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"I figured you would have heard."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"I figured you would have heard."

    old "Heard what?"
    new "Heard what?"

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"That big old horde that had been gathered under...what was that fella's name, Khan...something."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"That big old horde that had been gathered under...what was that fella's name, Khan...something."

    old "Hassar."
    new "Hassar."

    old "Sarah corrected the man. Unlike him, she would never forget the name of the man that had ruined her homeland and killed her brother."
    new "Sarah corrected the man. Unlike him, she would never forget the name of the man that had ruined her homeland and killed her brother."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Aah, yes, Hassar."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Aah, yes, Hassar."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Well, turns out savages can't ever play nice for too long."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Well, turns out savages can't ever play nice for too long."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Some clan or another started some trouble, probably over some trinket they robbed or some slave whore, and then it all broke down."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Some clan or another started some trouble, probably over some trinket they robbed or some slave whore, and then it all broke down."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Last I heard they're still infighting."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Last I heard they're still infighting."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"But one of the smaller clans got ran off towards the edges of the desert."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"But one of the smaller clans got ran off towards the edges of the desert."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"They paid some merchants to ship them across the sea and now they're being a pain in my ass."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"They paid some merchants to ship them across the sea and now they're being a pain in my ass."

    old "Sarah nodded as she listened."
    new "Sarah nodded as she listened."

    old "Her mortal enemy. The people that had destroyed her people. Lost to infighting."
    new "Her mortal enemy. The people that had destroyed her people. Lost to infighting."

    old "Sarah had imagined a million ways that her revenge might play out, only to learn that perhaps her glory had been stolen by some stranger."
    new "Sarah had imagined a million ways that her revenge might play out, only to learn that perhaps her glory had been stolen by some stranger."

    old "What about Rosanna?"
    new "What about Rosanna?"

    old "The officer looked up from a series of documents he had produced from his shirt."
    new "The officer looked up from a series of documents he had produced from his shirt."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Rosanna?"
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Rosanna?"

    old "Yes...is it safe?"
    new "Yes...is it safe?"

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"How the fuck should I know?"
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"How the fuck should I know?"

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"You think I keep track of every backwater province in the world?"
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"You think I keep track of every backwater province in the world?"

    old "To hear him describe her home as little more than a province stung, though to a Mythran, that was likely how most of the Union Kingdoms appeared."
    new "To hear him describe her home as little more than a province stung, though to a Mythran, that was likely how most of the Union Kingdoms appeared."

    old "I was only wondering."
    new "I was only wondering."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Well, best you use some of that brain power to get started on this."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Well, best you use some of that brain power to get started on this."

    old "He pushed the pile of documents into her hands."
    new "He pushed the pile of documents into her hands."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"These are the current drafts of our defensive lives."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"These are the current drafts of our defensive lives."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"I've made some notes on the sides, showing where I think our current weaknesses are."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"I've made some notes on the sides, showing where I think our current weaknesses are."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Look them over and start putting some men out on those positions."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Look them over and start putting some men out on those positions."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"I want to at least double our forces on all the main city gates."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"I want to at least double our forces on all the main city gates."

    old "Sarah nodded as she studied the map."
    new "Sarah nodded as she studied the map."

    old "Sure, I'll discuss it with my commander, but we'll manage to get that done by the end of the day."
    new "Sure, I'll discuss it with my commander, but we'll manage to get that done by the end of the day."

    old "Mythran Officer\" \"Great, well if that's all, I need to be on my way. Some recruit slept through his guard duty yesterday and I get to hand out the punishment."
    new "Mythran Officer\" \"Great, well if that's all, I need to be on my way. Some recruit slept through his guard duty yesterday and I get to hand out the punishment."

    old "The officer appeared more annoyed than anything else."
    new "The officer appeared more annoyed than anything else."

    old "Sarah watched as the officer took off in a steady march, on to his next appointment."
    new "Sarah watched as the officer took off in a steady march, on to his next appointment."

    old "Sarah finished reading the reports she had been handed and began to issue her own orders to the men."
    new "Sarah finished reading the reports she had been handed and began to issue her own orders to the men."

    old "One by one, groups of soldiers made their way towards their posting."
    new "One by one, groups of soldiers made their way towards their posting."

    old "By the time the remnants of the company had set up the camp among the ruins of the city, night was setting in."
    new "By the time the remnants of the company had set up the camp among the ruins of the city, night was setting in."

    old "Sarah was sitting on a stone block, near one of the campfires."
    new "Sarah was sitting on a stone block, near one of the campfires."

    old "The heat was a welcome relief from the cold of the desert night, but the truth was that none of it seemed to bother her anymore."
    new "The heat was a welcome relief from the cold of the desert night, but the truth was that none of it seemed to bother her anymore."

    old "After having survived the desert, everything else seemed easy."
    new "After having survived the desert, everything else seemed easy."

    old "Their supplies had been restocked from the Mythran supplies, and all the food and drink they had lacked for weeks, was now in abundance."
    new "Their supplies had been restocked from the Mythran supplies, and all the food and drink they had lacked for weeks, was now in abundance."

    old "The water in the desert had cleared the stress from her body, making her feel clean again."
    new "The water in the desert had cleared the stress from her body, making her feel clean again."

    old "Now, near the warming embers, she simply felt content."
    new "Now, near the warming embers, she simply felt content."

    old "They had survived. They would survive longer."
    new "They had survived. They would survive longer."

    old "Sitting on the block, staring into the fire, her mind roamed free."
    new "Sitting on the block, staring into the fire, her mind roamed free."

    old "She considered all that had happened in Bagrad. Both the obvious that she had expected, as well as the wicked and unexplainable."
    new "She considered all that had happened in Bagrad. Both the obvious that she had expected, as well as the wicked and unexplainable."

    old "The creature from the void. The spirit that spoke in riddles."
    new "The creature from the void. The spirit that spoke in riddles."

    old "Her fingers traced her chest."
    new "Her fingers traced her chest."

    old "She could feel the fate stone press againt her skin and stab out against the padded leather of her armor."
    new "She could feel the fate stone press againt her skin and stab out against the padded leather of her armor."

    old "More than once she had imagined casting the wicked thing into the sands of the desert. Forget it even existed."
    new "More than once she had imagined casting the wicked thing into the sands of the desert. Forget it even existed."

    old "And each time, a part of her had rebelled. Whatever it was, it must have meant something."
    new "And each time, a part of her had rebelled. Whatever it was, it must have meant something."

    old "Sarah thought about the strange stone that the spirit had urged her to take, but which she had allowed Vaelen to take."
    new "Sarah thought about the strange stone that the spirit had urged her to take, but which she had allowed Vaelen to take."

    old "Had she made a mistake?"
    new "Had she made a mistake?"

    old "She hardly knew what it was, and still, the object seemed to linger on her mind."
    new "She hardly knew what it was, and still, the object seemed to linger on her mind."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah heard a sound next to her."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah heard a sound next to her."

    old "When she looked up, she was not surprised. Only one person she knew made as little sound as this one."
    new "When she looked up, she was not surprised. Only one person she knew made as little sound as this one."

    old "The former princess of Bagrad smiled at her."
    new "The former princess of Bagrad smiled at her."

    old "The former princess of Rosanna smiled back at her."
    new "The former princess of Rosanna smiled back at her."

    old "Did you see the stars?"
    new "Did you see the stars?"

    old "What about the stars?"
    new "What about the stars?"

    old "They're sooo bright out here. I never saw them this bright before."
    new "They're sooo bright out here. I never saw them this bright before."

    old "Sarah looked up and saw the night sky."
    new "Sarah looked up and saw the night sky."

    old "But it was not like the sky as she knew it all. So vast and so plentiful, the stars bathed the sky in a cold blue light."
    new "But it was not like the sky as she knew it all. So vast and so plentiful, the stars bathed the sky in a cold blue light."

    old "How did I not see that till just now?"
    new "How did I not see that till just now?"

    old "Sarah genuinely wondered."
    new "Sarah genuinely wondered."

    old "She felt Samayra's hand on her shoulder."
    new "She felt Samayra's hand on her shoulder."

    old "Because you're too busy. Always working, on to this, onto the next."
    new "Because you're too busy. Always working, on to this, onto the next."

    old "You really should take a break, at least some of the time."
    new "You really should take a break, at least some of the time."

    old "My life was easy enough before I became a soldier. I think I'm just making up for all those years were I worked so little."
    new "My life was easy enough before I became a soldier. I think I'm just making up for all those years were I worked so little."

    old "Maybe it all averages out to a single ordinary life."
    new "Maybe it all averages out to a single ordinary life."

    old "She saw Samayra shake her head."
    new "She saw Samayra shake her head."

    old "You're a lot of things Sarah, but you're not ordinary."
    new "You're a lot of things Sarah, but you're not ordinary."

    old "Sarah looked at the girl, she suddenly noticed her flushed face, her wobbling pose."
    new "Sarah looked at the girl, she suddenly noticed her flushed face, her wobbling pose."

    old "Have you been drinking?"
    new "Have you been drinking?"

    old "Samayra suddenly laughed."
    new "Samayra suddenly laughed."

    old "Busted!"
    new "Busted!"

    old "But only a little, I promise!"
    new "But only a little, I promise!"

    old "Did you drink a little for your size, or a soldier's size?"
    new "Did you drink a little for your size, or a soldier's size?"

    old "She watched Samayra do the math in her head."
    new "She watched Samayra do the math in her head."

    old "Sarah laughed and gently pushed Samayra. Even the light nudge was enough to cause the girl to nearly tumble."
    new "Sarah laughed and gently pushed Samayra. Even the light nudge was enough to cause the girl to nearly tumble."

    old "Hey! Watch it, I'm delicate."
    new "Hey! Watch it, I'm delicate."

    old "That you are."
    new "That you are."

    old "You just make sure Kate doesn't come across you like this. I can't promise she won't try something."
    new "You just make sure Kate doesn't come across you like this. I can't promise she won't try something."

    old "She saw Samayra grin at her."
    new "She saw Samayra grin at her."

    old "What if I want someone to try something?"
    new "What if I want someone to try something?"

    old "The girl clumsily winked at her."
    new "The girl clumsily winked at her."

    old "You're drunk. I don't think this is a good idea..."
    new "You're drunk. I don't think this is a good idea..."

    old "Samayra leaned on her shoulder."
    new "Samayra leaned on her shoulder."

    old "Not that drunk..."
    new "Not that drunk..."

    old "Take Samayra back to your tent"
    new "Take Samayra back to your tent"

    old "Tell her to sleep it off"
    new "Tell her to sleep it off"

    old "Sarah gently pulled Samayra off her shoulder."
    new "Sarah gently pulled Samayra off her shoulder."

    old "Go, sleep it off."
    new "Go, sleep it off."

    old "But Sarah-"
    new "But Sarah-"

    old "Nothing's going to happen tonight, go and get some rest. That's an order."
    new "Nothing's going to happen tonight, go and get some rest. That's an order."

    old "Sarah heard Samayra sigh, frustrated."
    new "Sarah heard Samayra sigh, frustrated."

    old "She watched as the girl stumbled away to her tent, nearly half collapsing inside."
    new "She watched as the girl stumbled away to her tent, nearly half collapsing inside."

    old "It was better this way, Sarah thought."
    new "It was better this way, Sarah thought."

    old "The hours passed, the night grew deeper, when Sarah suddenly saw a familiar face passing by the campfire."
    new "The hours passed, the night grew deeper, when Sarah suddenly saw a familiar face passing by the campfire."

    old "Hey there, been lookin about for you."
    new "Hey there, been lookin about for you."

    old "Sarah could see her smile and she couldn't help but smile back at her."
    new "Sarah could see her smile and she couldn't help but smile back at her."

    old "They had been friends a lifetime ago, and it struck Sarah as remarkable that they had somehow found one another again."
    new "They had been friends a lifetime ago, and it struck Sarah as remarkable that they had somehow found one another again."

    old "A large world, but perhaps, not quite that big."
    new "A large world, but perhaps, not quite that big."

    old "I thought maybe you were still floating in that water in the desert."
    new "I thought maybe you were still floating in that water in the desert."

    old "Kate smiled as she walked passed the campfire and sat down next to Sarah."
    new "Kate smiled as she walked passed the campfire and sat down next to Sarah."

    old "Honestly, crossed my mind for half a second."
    new "Honestly, crossed my mind for half a second."

    old "Leave all this bullshit to the rest of you. But what can I say, I'm a glutton for punishment."
    new "Leave all this bullshit to the rest of you. But what can I say, I'm a glutton for punishment."

    old "Sarah watched Kate's eyes scan across the improvised campsite."
    new "Sarah watched Kate's eyes scan across the improvised campsite."

    old "Speaking of bullshit, what are we doing out here anyway?"
    new "Speaking of bullshit, what are we doing out here anyway?"

    old "Security. That's about all they told me. About all they're going to tell me as well, I think."
    new "Security. That's about all they told me. About all they're going to tell me as well, I think."

    old "What about Vaelen? Hasn't he told you anything?"
    new "What about Vaelen? Hasn't he told you anything?"

    old "Not much more than that either. Haven't even seen him since we got here. Who knows where he's off to."
    new "Not much more than that either. Haven't even seen him since we got here. Who knows where he's off to."

    old "I think he's just laying down for a bit."
    new "I think he's just laying down for a bit."

    old "Why do you think that?"
    new "Why do you think that?"

    old "Well, he ain't exactly popular with most of the men."
    new "Well, he ain't exactly popular with most of the men."

    old "Sarah hadn't been blind to that fact, but as a commander she always stood apart from the common soldier, more so than Kate who was an officer."
    new "Sarah hadn't been blind to that fact, but as a commander she always stood apart from the common soldier, more so than Kate who was an officer."

    old "What have you heard?"
    new "What have you heard?"

    old "Kate stared into the fire for a while."
    new "Kate stared into the fire for a while."

    old "I don't want to start anything."
    new "I don't want to start anything."

    old "We're just talking, friends."
    new "We're just talking, friends."

    old "Kate looked at her, rolling her eyes."
    new "Kate looked at her, rolling her eyes."

    old "You're a terrible liar. But fine."
    new "You're a terrible liar. But fine."

    old "Most of the men were riding high after the victory on Bagrad. Hell, most of them kept it up as we marched on into the desert."
    new "Most of the men were riding high after the victory on Bagrad. Hell, most of them kept it up as we marched on into the desert."

    old "But it really started when they were ordered to leave their loot behind."
    new "But it really started when they were ordered to leave their loot behind."

    old "For most of them, it was more money than they'd ever seen in their lives."
    new "For most of them, it was more money than they'd ever seen in their lives."

    old "I've been soldiering for a while now, and even I can't recall a haul that good."
    new "I've been soldiering for a while now, and even I can't recall a haul that good."

    old "Kate paused for a moment, gathering her thoughts."
    new "Kate paused for a moment, gathering her thoughts."

    old "Well, after that order the rumors started. People saying he'd lost it. Small stuff at first..."
    new "Well, after that order the rumors started. People saying he'd lost it. Small stuff at first..."

    old "But as it went on and on, and the food ran out, and the wagons broke down and...well you remember."
    new "But as it went on and on, and the food ran out, and the wagons broke down and...well you remember."

    old "It all just kept piling up."
    new "It all just kept piling up."

    old "By the end of it, some people, and I'm not going to name names and I'll deny this if you ever try to tell someone, but they were openly talking about killing him."
    new "By the end of it, some people, and I'm not going to name names and I'll deny this if you ever try to tell someone, but they were openly talking about killing him."

    old "Sarah knew things had gotten bad, but she hadn't imagined that bad."
    new "Sarah knew things had gotten bad, but she hadn't imagined that bad."

    old "They said that?"
    new "They said that?"

    old "A few, the dumbest of the lot, but still. This shit always starts from the bottom and rises up."
    new "A few, the dumbest of the lot, but still. This shit always starts from the bottom and rises up."

    old "Honestly, if we had still been out there a week from now, I figure we actually would have had a mutiny."
    new "Honestly, if we had still been out there a week from now, I figure we actually would have had a mutiny."

    old "Sarah was quiet as she listened to Kate explain it from her perspective."
    new "Sarah was quiet as she listened to Kate explain it from her perspective."

    old "When she was done, she simply nodded."
    new "When she was done, she simply nodded."

    old "I think I understand."
    new "I think I understand."

    old "Thank the gods we managed to reach this place before it all broke down."
